The paper uses machine learning and natural language processing techniques to predict safety outcomes in the construction industry. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as the study involves developing models to assist humans in making decisions related to safety. The use of natural language processing (NLP) to extract attributes from raw incident reports suggests that the paper could also be classified under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the study involves predicting safety outcomes, which could be considered a form of risk assessment, placing it under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) or software engineering (cs.SE).
